  "prompt": "I was booking ticket from IRCTC but due to technical problem, I fail to book the tckt, bt amt got debited from account. By when would that b refunded?",
  "response": "If you have faced an issue while booking a ticket on IRCTC and the amount was debited from your account without the ticket being confirmed, here's what you can do:\n\n1. Refund Timeline:\n- Typically, the refund is processed within 3-7 working days\n- In some cases, it might take up to 10-15 days depending on your bank\n\n2. Steps to Follow:\n- Keep the transaction reference number/screenshot\n- Contact IRCTC customer care\n- Raise a complaint on their website or app\n- Call their helpline number: 139\n\n3. Bank Refund Process:\n- If IRCTC doesn't refund, contact your bank\n- Provide them transaction details\n- Request them to initiate a chargeback\n\n4. Important Contact Details:\n- IRCTC Helpline: 139\n- IRCTC Customer Support Email: care@irctc.co.in\n\n5. Required Documents:\n- Transaction screenshot\n- Transaction ID\n- Date and time of transaction\n\nTip: Always keep transaction proof and follow up regularly for faster resolution.",
